-- Anglo Platinum, Sasol May Move: South African Equity Preview
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 2010-12-29T06:03:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/anglogold-anglo-platinum-sasol-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  fell for the
third day in four, losing 24.75, or 0.1 percent, to 32,012.31 at
the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Anglo Platinum Ltd.  (AMS SJ): Platinum fell as much as 0.5
percent to $1,745.75 an ounce. Anglo Platinum, the world’s
largest producer of the metal, retreated 1.81 rand, or 0.3
percent, to 682.97 rand.  Sasol Ltd.  (SOL SJ): Crude oil decreased as much as 0.3
percent to $91.20 a barrel. Sasol, the world’s biggest maker of
motor fuel from coal, closed unchanged at 339 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of South African
companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) gained 0.6 percent to $25.42.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) added 3.1 percent to $49.54. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) shed 1 percent to $79.71. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) closed unchanged at $4.76. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI US)
rose 2 percent to $17.97. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY US)
advanced 2 percent to $12.49. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY
US) didn’t change, closing at $34.20. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
declined 0.4 percent to $5.18. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) added 2.3
percent to $50.66.  To contact the reporter on this story:
